# MWCC compiler registry. Read by:
#   * build.rs                   -> generates the in-binary Rust registry
#   * scripts/fetch-toolchain.sh -> fetches + SHA-verifies each mwcceppc.exe
#
# One Lambda is deployed per row (for per-version AWS metrics), all running the
# SAME shared bootstrap; the row's `id` is passed as the MWCC_VERSION env var to
# select which vendored mwcceppc.exe that Lambda runs. Those per-version Lambdas
# live in template.yaml (hand-maintained — keep them in sync with this list, one
# Lambda per row, in the same order).
#
# Columns are pipe-delimited:  id|family|dir|token|sha1|label
#   id     decomp.me compiler id; the MWCC_VERSION env value for that Lambda
#   family bundle top-level dir (GC | Wii); also the vendor/ subdir
#   dir    bundle version dir; vendored at vendor/compiler/<family>/<dir>/
#   token  URL version segment -> /compile/mwcc/<token>/<action> (unique, url-safe)
#   sha1   SHA-1 of that version's mwcceppc.exe (build-time verification)
#   label  human label for /health
#
# Source: decomp.dev compilers bundle (see COMPILERS_TAG in fetch-toolchain.sh).
# The license DLL (lmgr326b.dll for GC, lmgr8c.dll for Wii/3.0a) is one shared
# file across every version, pinned once in fetch-toolchain.sh — not listed here.
#
# Default version (owns the legacy flat routes): mwcc_247_92 (GC MW 2.0).
# Not in this bundle tag: GC MW 1.2.5e (mwcc_233_163e). ProDG is a separate gcc
# toolchain (multi-exe pipeline), not wired here.
